<dl id="n35014b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35014b">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35014b"> 14(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> good voice to beg / bacon</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">BACON. He has saved his bacon; he has escaped. He has a good voice to beg bacon; a saying in ridicule of a bad voice. <small> Captain Francis Grose, <a name="FGCD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FGCD"><cite title="source">A Classical Dictionary of the Vulgar Tongue</cite></a> (1785) BAG</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
